#  Maintained by Joachim Breitner (nomeata/arbtt).  349 GH stars.
#  arbtt is the AUTOMATIC RULE-BASED TIME TRACKER for Linux/macOS/
#  Windows — captures snapshots of your desktop activity (active
#  window title + idle time) every 60 seconds, then lets you write
#  classification rules in a domain-specific language to categorize
#  your time post-hoc.  Unlike traditional time trackers (Toggl,
#  Harvest, RescueTime) that require manual start/stop, arbtt records
#  everything passively and you decide retroactively how to slice
#  the data.  Sister tools: Toggl Track (manual, commercial),
#  ActivityWatch (in corpus via _aw-server), RescueTime (commercial),
#  watson (CLI time tracker, in corpus).
#
